*** Push file to GitHub Repository ***

Steps to be followed:
1.	Create a GitHub repository
2.	Create a repository on the local machine
3.	Push the changes from the local repository to GitHub
4.	Check the status of the local and remote repository


1. Create a GitHub repository
    ** Create repo in github.com
    
2. Create a repository on the local machine
      $ mkdir project
      $ cd project
      $ echo "Create new file for my project" >> README.md
      $ git init
      $ git add README
      $ git commit -m "File added"
      
3. Push the changes from the local repository to GitHub
      $ git push -u origin main
      
4. Check the status of the local and remote repository
      $ git status
    *** Go to github.com, and check the remote repository
      
